description:
This place is extraordinary.  Unpretentious, beautifully prepared, and exquisitely flavored food - with a great wine and beer list to boot.  

Highlights included:
-Burrata, lobster, and heirloom tomato salad (are you kidding me?);
-Incredible mussels (I don't even typically like mussels);
-Red trout with grilled asparagus, grilled pea leaves, and fava leaves (this was exceptional, and proves that the chef can do both hot and cold plates well);
-Seafood chowder for dessert (buttery and perfect early fall treat).

I also love the ambiance and service.  We had a great waitress who made some stellar recommendations. 

I cannot recommend this place highly enough.  My new favorite for a celebratory dinner.

I found this great place through sheer luck,
The flavors left me thunderstruck;
In SF city
It's in my top three;
And oysters make me want to....uh....hug everyone.
